He walked away with sorrow because he had many possessions.

471
00:30:28.640 --> 00:30:30.960
So his unwillingness to let go of it showed

472
00:30:30.960 --> 00:30:32.920
that he really wasn't wanting to follow Jesus

473
00:30:32.960 --> 00:30:35.840
because he was holding on to those things instead.

474
00:30:35.840 --> 00:30:38.160
All right, positive example.

475
00:30:38.160 --> 00:30:40.760
2 Corinthians chapter eight.

476
00:30:40.760 --> 00:30:44.760
The apostle Paul is going around and he's taking up a collection

477
00:30:44.760 --> 00:30:48.720
for Christians who are suffering with poverty in Judea.

478
00:30:49.760 --> 00:30:52.880
And he's about to go to the church at Corinth

479
00:30:52.880 --> 00:30:55.080
and receive money from them as well.

480
00:30:55.080 --> 00:30:56.760
He says, let me give you an example

481
00:30:56.760 --> 00:30:58.520
of what I've seen recently.

482
00:30:58.520 --> 00:31:01.280
It's the church of, the churches in Macedonia,

483
00:31:01.320 --> 00:31:04.320
they were also struggling with poverty as well.

484
00:31:04.320 --> 00:31:08.640
He said, but they insisted that they take part

485
00:31:08.640 --> 00:31:10.960
in this collection that was being taken up

486
00:31:10.960 --> 00:31:13.040
for the believers in Judea.

487
00:31:13.040 --> 00:31:15.400
And he says, here's why that they insisted

488
00:31:15.400 --> 00:31:18.680
that they take part in giving to others as well.

489
00:31:18.680 --> 00:31:22.680
He says it was because of their overflowing joy.

490
00:31:23.520 --> 00:31:25.600
And then he goes on in 2 Corinthians chapter nine

491
00:31:25.600 --> 00:31:27.040
saying that we, this is a grace

492
00:31:27.040 --> 00:31:28.120
that should be true of all of us.

493
00:31:28.120 --> 00:31:31.080
We're all called to be cheerful givers.

494
00:31:31.080 --> 00:31:33.240
So there's a principle that's there in the New Testament

495
00:31:33.240 --> 00:31:37.040
that we are called to be a giving people

496
00:31:37.040 --> 00:31:39.240
as followers of Christ.

497
00:31:39.240 --> 00:31:42.160
But we're not giving from a place of obligation

498
00:31:42.160 --> 00:31:45.280
but out of a heart of joy.

499
00:31:45.280 --> 00:31:49.000
We do it gladly because our treasure is in heaven.

500
00:31:49.000 --> 00:31:51.840
We know that the Lord can use that

501
00:31:51.840 --> 00:31:55.700
for his good purposes in the world.

502
00:31:56.680 --> 00:31:58.640
So we do it cheerfully.

503
00:31:58.640 --> 00:32:00.320
Now I don't know what the specifics of that

504
00:32:00.320 --> 00:32:03.160
will look like for you, but let me just say

505
00:32:03.160 --> 00:32:05.320
it would be good for all of us to prayerfully consider

506
00:32:05.320 --> 00:32:07.800
like Lord, what would you have me to do

507
00:32:07.800 --> 00:32:10.960
in this area of my life?

508
00:32:13.320 --> 00:32:15.000
When it comes to that area,

509
00:32:15.000 --> 00:32:17.400
we're giving of ourselves in other areas too.

510
00:32:17.400 --> 00:32:20.040
We do it because of the treasure that we see in Jesus.

511
00:32:20.040 --> 00:32:23.220
I don't think Terry Herbert regretted

512
00:32:23.220 --> 00:32:27.680
spending two pounds and 50 pence for dollars

513
00:32:27.680 --> 00:32:29.520
on that metal detector.

514
00:32:29.520 --> 00:32:32.360
Once he had received the treasure,

515
00:32:32.360 --> 00:32:34.920
it was like nothing in comparison.

516
00:32:34.920 --> 00:32:37.120
You know, when we see Christ for who he truly is,

517
00:32:37.120 --> 00:32:40.520
we gladly surrender the whole of ourselves to him

518
00:32:40.520 --> 00:32:42.820
because he's far greater than we can imagine.

519
00:32:44.400 --> 00:32:47.000
So as we're moving to communion to now,

520
00:32:47.000 --> 00:32:50.320
now I wanna ask you what are you treasuring?

521
00:32:51.600 --> 00:32:52.440
We're gonna pray together,

522
00:32:52.440 --> 00:32:54.760
but as you come to the Lord in prayer,

523
00:32:54.760 --> 00:32:57.320
just ask yourself the question, what has my heart?

524
00:32:57.320 --> 00:33:01.000
What am I looking to to satisfy the longings of my heart?

525
00:33:02.200 --> 00:33:04.600
Take some time looking to Christ,

526
00:33:05.720 --> 00:33:07.480
praying that you might know him as your treasure,

527
00:33:07.480 --> 00:33:09.280
that you might delight in him.

528
00:33:11.280 --> 00:33:13.740
Hear these words about what Jesus did for us.

529
00:33:14.920 --> 00:33:16.600
Second Corinthians eight, once again, it says,

530
00:33:16.600 --> 00:33:19.520
for you know the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ,

531
00:33:19.520 --> 00:33:22.800
that though he was rich, yet for your sake,

532
00:33:22.800 --> 00:33:26.040
he became poor that through your poverty,

533
00:33:26.040 --> 00:33:29.680
or by his poverty, you might become rich.

534
00:33:30.520 --> 00:33:34.000
So Jesus took on the poverty of our state.

535
00:33:34.000 --> 00:33:38.600
He took on our humanity, our sin, and our death.

536
00:33:39.880 --> 00:33:44.440
He willingly surrendered his life on the cross

537
00:33:44.440 --> 00:33:47.360
and this bread is symbolically reminding us

538
00:33:47.360 --> 00:33:48.640
of what he did on the cross

539
00:33:48.640 --> 00:33:53.640
because there on the cross, his body was broken for us.

540
00:33:57.040 --> 00:33:59.800
And as we partake in the bread,

541
00:33:59.800 --> 00:34:01.240
we're reminding ourselves,

542
00:34:01.240 --> 00:34:03.640
remembering what he has done for us on the cross.

543
00:34:04.960 --> 00:34:06.920
Not only was his body broken on the cross,

544
00:34:06.920 --> 00:34:09.280
his blood was shed on the cross.

545
00:34:09.280 --> 00:34:10.640
And as we drink of this cup,

546
00:34:10.640 --> 00:34:14.640
we are reminded of his blood that was shed for us

547
00:34:14.640 --> 00:34:16.840
upon the cross.

548
00:34:19.840 --> 00:34:22.200
So we surrender our lives to him

549
00:34:22.200 --> 00:34:27.200
because he first surrendered his life for us.

550
00:34:28.520 --> 00:34:33.520
We treasure him because he decided to make us his own

551
00:34:34.760 --> 00:34:37.760
by dying in our place and rising again.

552
00:34:37.760 --> 00:34:39.760
So before we come to the table, let's pray together.

553
00:34:39.760 --> 00:34:41.480
Let's take a moment and quiet prayer

554
00:34:41.480 --> 00:34:44.480
and then I'll pray and give thanks for the bread and wine.

